# Enforce LF line endings repo-wide.
#
# Why: this is a multi-platform Python project. Without explicit rules,
# Git on Windows can auto-convert LF<->CRLF on checkout/commit
# (`core.autocrlf=true`), which produces noise in `git status` and
# can confuse review tools that expect one or the other.
#
# Effect: every text file is stored as LF in git AND checked out as LF
# everywhere -- no more "LF will be replaced by CRLF" warnings on
# `git add` from Windows machines, and any viewer that walks the raw
# blob sees the same byte stream the linter / interpreter sees.
#
# Existing blobs in the repo are ALREADY LF (verified). This file
# locks that in for future contributors.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files: never touch line endings.
*.png         binary
*.jpg         binary
*.jpeg        binary
*.gif         binary
*.ico         binary
*.pdf         binary
*.zip         binary
*.gz          binary
*.tar         binary
*.whl         binary
